    public void createBufferStrategy(@Refinement("AtLeastOne(numBuffers)") int numBuffers, BufferCapabilities caps);

    @StateRefinement(to = "notdisplayable(this)")
    public void dispose();

    @StateRefinement(from = "notdisplayable(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "displayable(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "visible(this)", to = "displayable(this)")
    public void hide();

    @StateRefinement(from = "notdisplayable(this)", to = "displayable(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "displayable(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "visible(this)")
    public void pack();

    @StateRefinement(from = "notdisplayable(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "displayable(this)")
    public void setLocationByPlatform(boolean locationByPlatform);

    @StateRefinement(from = "notdisplayable(this)")
    public void setType(Window.Type type);

    @StateRefinement(from = "notdisplayable(this)", to = "visible(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "displayable(this)", to = "visible(this)")
    @StateRefinement(from = "visible(this)", to = "displayable(this)")
    public void setVisible(boolean b);

    @StateRefinement(to = "visible(this)")
    public void show();

}
```

**Key design decisions:**

1. **`@RefinementAlias("AtLeastOne(int n) { n >= 1 }")`** - Created because `numBuffers >= 1` is required by both overloads of `createBufferStrategy` (the JSON docs state `IllegalArgumentException` if numBuffers < 1).

2. **`createBufferStrategy` restricted to `displayable` and `visible` states** - The Mermaid note explicitly states "createBufferStrategy() requires Displayable or Visible," so `NotDisplayable` is correctly excluded via `from` constraints.

3. **`setType` restricted to `notdisplayable` only** - The Mermaid note states "setType() only valid in NotDisplayable state," and the JSON docs confirm it "can only be called while the window is not displayable."

4. **`setLocationByPlatform` restricted to `notdisplayable` and `displayable`** - The Mermaid note states "setLocationByPlatform(true) forbidden when Visible," which is encoded by omitting the `Visible` state from `from` constraints.

5. **`dispose()` callable from any state** - Goes to `notdisplayable` from all three states, so no `from` constraint is needed.

